reviewText: Very short documentary: run time is about 10 minutes.  I didn't learn anything from the video that I didn't already know.  As someone who has worked with traditional Hopis, I know their customs and had friends who lived in Hotevilla.  I expected more from Autobiography of a Hopi.
This short educational film was produced in cooperation with the Hopi traditional council in Hotevilla, Arizona, telling a Hopi story very simple to understand in the light of Standing Rock.
Unfortunately I haven't had a chance to watch this dvd yet, but will review at a later date, so the rating is a guess!!
